    {
      "id": "12eff930e66bca692decca261bc4673889ef10d4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-03-19 16:57:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nThe error message is improved, but I wonder if it is better to just get rid of this entirely?\n\nThe other thing that is a bit strange, is that I thought the \".lustre\" directory should not appear in \"ls -a\" output for Lustre, which would avoid it being seen by programs that are traversing the filesystem.  That doesn't seem to be the case with 2.4, but it would be worthwhile to check 2.1 or 2.2 to see if .lustre was hidden then.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
